<br>
  I don't have the most charming personality, but I always thought this was an exaggeration, but it's been happening with alarming frequency lately.  Not that this is anything new to those who have experienced.   I was ready to delete my wizard after 2 nights in a row of this...<br>
  <br>
  It's even when worse when I see groups training something because they didn't have a well played wizard in their group, or even an enchanter.  What is wrong with these people? Wizards are the pefect class for dealing with overpulls, and if all else fails, they can evacaute. (Druids may or may not have us beat here, nerfing druids abilitiy to teleport and nuke into non-existanc has been a long needed change in my opinion.)<br>
<br>
    Heck, I'm even a master baker, because some races seem to have fun with things like cookies, rat kabobs, and batwing crunchies...<br>
<br>
    Is this another hurdle I must encounter as I go up? I recently hit 42nd Circle, but teleporting around looking for a group, isn't exactly fun either.  I've started to go /role so I don't get inane requests for teleports.  (There are times when I let it be known that it's 100pp per teleport request, if people are likely to spam me with them -- not that this helps.)<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uberylshadowhawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beryl Shadowhawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/2/01 10:37:07 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.unlv.edu/faculty/engstrom/images/bcard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting sick of going through 6 zones looking...</span><hr size=1> Well, it can be hard to find a group some days.  If you can get a regular group setup the game is a lot more fun.  If you have to go the pickup route and run into a streak of bad luck, just stay bound near a good solo area.  If you can't get a group after 15-30 mins of trying hit the solo stuff for a bit.  It might be your the wrong level, wrong place, or wrong time or all/any of the above.  If you have a bad rep, you might need to write off the end game of EQ.  The end game of EQ is all about friends and cooperation.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukhaelwizzie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>khaelwizzie</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/3/01 8:38:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting sick of going through 6 zones looking...</span><hr size=1> Good advice, Beryl. Everyone is going to have off days, sometimes even a string of off days; the trick is not to let it get you down and either head off to do some soloing (quad kiting!) like Beryl suggested or go do a quest or help some lower level friends. Best way to avoid looking for groups is to have a set group that meets and hunts together regularly or form groups yourselves instead of looking to join them.. both of these ways work great for not having to run around looking for groups yourself. <p><FONT COLOR=purple><b>~Khael</b></FONT><br>
<FONT COLOR=silver><i>Proud Officer of Affliction</i></FONT><br><FONT COLOR=silver><i>Sorcerer of Erollisi Marr</i></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulenadaynastardew.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenadayna Stardew</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/3/01 9:25:49 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=c:\windows\desktop\lena.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting sick of going through 6 zones looking...</span><hr size=1>   I also forgot that when you first enter a zone, wizards often have problems getting groups.   I've often made friends/allies afterwards (and enemies, but this will happen to everybody -- and I really did need to tell a halfling druid off last night.  But getting the party killed because your not healing and playing the wrong class - is in my opinion needed.)<br>
<br>
   Kiting is something I learned how to do fairly late though...  Not up to quad-kiting yet, but I can kite two or 3 things successfully if I try.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eovandall>Eovandall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/12/01 9:20:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting sick of going through 6 zones looking...</span><hr size=1> And I have often found that, if I cannot find a group, I can start my own (in most zones, at most times).<br>
So often I have been in a zone (already in a group), and a friend bops into that zone.  They start lfg.<br>
Minutes later, they are still lfg.  They complain to me, that no one wants them.  (This might be a wizzie or not.....it happens to lots of people, from time to time.)  But...as they have been lfg, others have been<br>
lfg at the same time!  In between my group's pulls, I start telling these folks, and get them organized into<br>
a group (usually next to mine!).  As time goes by, this little ragtag group evolves into a nice, well-balanced<br>
killing machine, and my friend is amazed.  And this has happened several times.<br>
People tend to get stuck in a rut.  They think, &quot;I am lfg.&quot;  And that's it, then......lfg for 30 minutes.  Agh!<br>
When they are shown they can think outside the box, then the world opens for them.  Heheheheh<br>
